WEBVTT

00:50.818 --> 00:51.319
Well, good morning.

00:51.339 --> 00:52.643
Good morning, Sugar Creek family.

00:52.683 --> 00:54.608
It's so good to be with you today.

00:54.629 --> 01:02.510
Hey, I want to welcome our Missouri City family, Richmond Rosenberg, all of you online, and everyone here at Sugar Land.

01:02.671 --> 01:05.298
It's so good to be back home here at Sugar Creek.

01:05.410 --> 01:21.824
Hey, if you're new to sugar creek in the last three and a half years, this might be our first time to me, but I am part of your family, your extended global family of people who have been formed and shaped here at ministry at Sugar Creek and just sent to a different part of the world to serve Jesus.

01:22.465 --> 01:26.889
And then just so thankful to Pastor Mark for the chance to be back with you for a couple of weeks.

01:27.249 --> 01:35.396
Now Stacy and I and our children Avery and Liam, we live in North Dallas and we have the joy of pastoring a church called Bentry Bible Fellowship

01:35.376 --> 01:38.361
And we're just thankful to open up God's word with you today.

01:38.742 --> 01:44.551
Now, last two Sundays, you had Pastor Eric Witten, who did a great series on marriage.

01:45.032 --> 01:50.180
And today, we are taking a hard turn to talk about politics.

01:51.242 --> 01:53.586
Yes, you heard me correctly.

01:53.698 --> 01:56.120
Now, if you're like, this is your first Sunday here.

01:56.160 --> 01:58.462
You're like, what in the world did I just step into?

01:58.502 --> 01:59.343
Don't pack your bags.

01:59.423 --> 02:00.364
Just quiet yet.

02:00.844 --> 02:01.925
Give me a few minutes.

02:02.265 --> 02:08.271
We're going to be OK. Now, actually, Pastor Eric and I, we both live in North Dallas just a few minutes from each other.

02:08.311 --> 02:12.554
And we were grabbing lunch a few months ago, talking about being here with you in July.

02:12.594 --> 02:15.417
And he told me he was doing a series on marriage.

02:15.997 --> 02:18.580
And I said, well, Pastor Mark, let me do one on politics.

02:18.620 --> 02:21.022
I wish I could do the marriage, but I guess I'll do politics.

02:21.302 --> 02:23.684
But I texted Pastor Mark afterwards and say,

02:23.664 --> 02:26.407
Pastor, Eric and I decided we're gonna combine our series.

02:27.087 --> 02:31.291
And for the whole month of July, we're gonna talk about how to keep politics out of your marriage, if that's okay with you.

02:32.252 --> 02:35.755
No, he didn't sign off on that, but maybe next summer I'll come back and do that.

02:37.257 --> 02:41.341
Now, I'm gonna level set some expectations of what this series is and what it's not.

02:42.321 --> 02:51.410
This isn't a series where I convince people who vote differently than you that they are wrong, because this isn't just for the other party,

02:51.938 --> 03:05.215
This series is for all of us together, as one faith community, one church family, to enter into a united mindset of how we enter and engage in the world of politics.

03:05.955 --> 03:10.381
So look at somebody next to you on all campuses and just tell them, this series is for me.

03:10.461 --> 03:11.322
Come on, go ahead and do it.

03:11.342 --> 03:12.283
This series is for me.

03:12.303 --> 03:20.914
Now, look to your second choice, your person you did not look at, and I tell the other person, your second choice, this series is for me.

03:20.994 --> 03:23.938
So this isn't for the other part, this is for all of us together.

03:23.958 --> 03:31.948
And second of all, this series is not to encourage you or to ask you to disengage from the world of politics.

03:32.428 --> 03:33.029
No, no, not at all.

03:33.349 --> 03:46.706
There are some serious things involved in our country today, some political issues that are significant for our nation, many issues that have deep theological and moral implications.

03:48.007 --> 03:50.130
And God instituted government

03:50.274 --> 03:55.481
to restrain evil and serve his purpose on the earth, to serve his will on the earth.

03:56.122 --> 04:05.336
So when God isn't being honored and evil isn't restrained, we have a responsibility and a calling to be engaged, to speak up.

04:06.337 --> 04:16.772
If God calls you to run for office or to be engaged at whatever level, certainly the responsibility and the privilege to vote based on convictions that God has given us.

04:16.792 --> 04:18.194
So this is not for that either.

04:19.618 --> 04:33.255
This series is for all of us to discover how do we as Christ's followers enter the world of politics differently because we have been shaped and formed by Jesus.

04:34.336 --> 04:45.650
How do we as Christians uniquely engage in the topic of politics because we are walking with Jesus and we have been formed and shaped by Jesus?

04:46.338 --> 04:51.486
When you come to know Jesus and you begin to walk with Him, every area of your life changes.

04:52.047 --> 05:01.402
Like you engage in your career, in your singleness, in your marriage, in your finances, in the relationships of your life differently because you were walking with Jesus.

05:01.422 --> 05:03.685
There was this old way of doing life.

05:04.847 --> 05:11.698
And now that you've met Jesus, there is a gospel-informed way of doing life, and that applies to politics too.

05:12.354 --> 05:17.740
Jesus reframes how we think about and engage in the world of politics.

05:18.581 --> 05:30.393
Now, if you follow Jesus and nothing about your life has changed, you may be more a fan of Jesus than you are his follower, because following him changes everything about who we are.

05:32.195 --> 05:38.482
Eight days ago, we witnessed the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump.

05:40.482 --> 05:46.949
And it was just another indication of how deeply wrong things are in the world of politics in our nation.

05:50.493 --> 05:53.897
In our democracy like ours, we don't deal with difference through violence.

05:53.997 --> 05:54.717
It is not our way.

05:56.239 --> 05:58.141
But that's the condition we have found ourselves in.

05:59.022 --> 06:06.290
Deep hatred, vitriol, hostility and a lack of civility and engaging in the world of politics.

06:07.682 --> 06:26.167
In 2021, there was a survey done by the University of Maryland and the Washington Post, and they found across a country that 81% of people who have served in public office experienced some sort of violence, harassment, and threats in their time of office.

06:26.367 --> 06:28.029
81% experienced that.

06:29.291 --> 06:37.522
The same survey found that one out of three Americans, this is staggering to me, one out of three Americans,

06:38.018 --> 06:46.110
Believe that violence against government is a justifiable means for political gain.

06:48.674 --> 06:53.922
What out of three Americans believe that violence is a justifiable means?

06:54.503 --> 07:02.915
That might be the most ever in our nation where people believe that violence is okay and good and justified for political means.

07:03.977 --> 07:07.442
It's a sad reality we find ourselves in and I think partly

07:08.258 --> 07:13.228
It's because we are more politically literate than we are biblically literate.

07:14.871 --> 07:23.708
We are shaped by social media, discipled by our news channels, formed and identified more by our politics than we are by Jesus, His Word and the Holy Spirit of God.

07:26.232 --> 07:29.138
And we are invited in this series

07:30.306 --> 07:39.020
To remember that we are not Republicans first or Democrats or independents, we are first and foremost citizens of heaven following a King named Jesus.

07:39.080 --> 07:40.723
And we belong to his kingdom.

07:40.783 --> 07:41.464
That's it.

07:41.484 --> 07:44.308
That's our highest allegiance, our highest devotion.

07:47.734 --> 07:55.346
And what that means is that we may be divided in our politics, but we can be united in our posture.

07:56.578 --> 08:00.163
We may be divided in how we view certain issues in the world.

08:00.223 --> 08:05.470
We may be divided in our politics, but we don't have to be divided in our posture to one another.

08:05.750 --> 08:07.973
We can be united in our posture.

08:09.435 --> 08:11.859
Our posture towards one another is unity.

08:12.700 --> 08:16.885
We may have differing opinions, but we are one in Christ as a faith family.

08:17.106 --> 08:18.488
We are one in Jesus.

08:18.688 --> 08:22.333
So our posture towards one another horizontally is unity.

08:22.633 --> 08:23.314
Love.

08:24.482 --> 08:27.986
Our posture towards the world is compassion and the great commission.

08:28.327 --> 08:35.856
If the great commission matters to you, then people are not enemies to be alienated or eliminated.

08:35.876 --> 08:42.585
They are souls to love and lead to life change in Christ.

08:43.526 --> 08:46.930
And if you view people as enemies, you'll never love them into the kingdom.

08:48.578 --> 08:54.885
Our posture towards God is a deep abiding trust in him that he is sovereign over the universe.

08:54.905 --> 08:56.306
He is on the throne.

08:56.506 --> 09:00.390
He is king and he is our only savior.

09:01.752 --> 09:07.918
In seasons like we're in today, you'll hear politicians claim that Jesus is exclusively on their side.

09:07.938 --> 09:08.819
But I got news for you.

09:09.019 --> 09:10.461
Jesus didn't come to take sides.

09:10.681 --> 09:11.662
He came to take over.

09:11.922 --> 09:15.346
He exists in a category called holy, holy, holy.

09:15.490 --> 09:20.358
And he invites you and I, choose for yourself this day whom you will serve.

09:20.418 --> 09:31.055
And may we say with Joshua, as for me and my household, for our church, for our faith community, now we will serve Jesus and no one else.

09:32.257 --> 09:32.818
No one else.

09:34.741 --> 09:42.834
So just imagine the difference Christians could make if the people who follow the same crucified and risen Jesus

09:43.106 --> 09:46.270
Stepped into politics entirely different than the rest of the world.

09:48.493 --> 10:01.269
The tone difference, the life difference, the people on both sides of the aisle would be so challenged in the best way possible by people who are shaped by Jesus and filled with the Spirit.

10:02.030 --> 10:05.254
Maybe divided in politics, but united in posture.

10:06.716 --> 10:11.122
And when we are united in our posture toward one another, toward God, toward the world,

10:11.682 --> 10:13.684
we can handle differences in politics.

10:14.525 --> 10:15.205
I got good news for you.

10:15.566 --> 10:17.167
You don't have to lose friends every four years.

10:17.828 --> 10:21.311
You don't have to skip Thanksgiving this November.

10:21.372 --> 10:32.983
When there is a posture that binds us together or heartbeat around the gospel and around God's kingdom, we don't have to ruin relationships.

10:35.445 --> 10:40.210
There's a question that we get asked often around this time of the year.

10:40.322 --> 10:40.923
or season.

10:41.263 --> 10:41.964
And that's this question.

10:42.345 --> 10:45.469
What would Jesus do if he lived in our day?

10:46.350 --> 10:48.213
Like how would he identify politically?

10:48.313 --> 10:51.037
What would he do if he were alive today?

10:51.257 --> 10:51.978
Now here's the good news.

10:52.299 --> 10:54.923
You don't have to wonder what Jesus would do.

10:55.483 --> 11:00.210
We can actually look at the gospels and see what Jesus did do in his day.

11:00.866 --> 11:06.812
Jesus lived in one of the most contentious and polarizing political times in Jewish history.

11:07.052 --> 11:09.875
In fact, in his day, there weren't just two different parties.

11:09.895 --> 11:11.537
There were six different parties.

11:12.538 --> 11:19.104
People with varying differing ideologies are on what was best for Israel and how to engage with the Roman government.

11:20.145 --> 11:21.867
The divided politics of Jesus' day.

11:22.328 --> 11:28.754
You had, for instance, the Sadducees who held onto political power by accommodating to the Roman Empire.

11:29.346 --> 11:38.740
Then you had the Pharisees who had a strict adherence to the Mosaic law, and they believed that Moses' 10 commandments and God's laws were to be the law of the land.

11:39.601 --> 11:56.426
Then you had the zealots who saw themselves as a violent, resistance army seeking to kill as many Romans as they possibly could because they felt that violence and resistance in that hostility way and that hostile way was the only path to victory.

11:57.808 --> 11:58.930
Then you had their scenes.

11:59.586 --> 12:03.630
who withdrew from social and political life altogether.

12:03.671 --> 12:07.415
They moved up to the mountains wanting nothing to do with their world.

12:08.216 --> 12:16.665
Then you had the Herodians who didn't side with Caesar, but they sided with King Herod as Caesar appointed, and they held on to his dynasty.

12:17.926 --> 12:24.474
Then you had the Roman Empire who ruled the Jewish people from 63 BC all the way to the 4th century, a long time.

12:26.055 --> 12:28.498
And this was an oppressive government.

12:28.802 --> 12:29.663
for the Jewish people.

12:30.945 --> 12:42.599
Jesus grew up in Nazareth, and in his day, while he lived in Nazareth, there were multiple anti-imperial uprisings and insurrections against the Roman Empire.

12:42.939 --> 12:49.367
Jesus literally stepped into a contentious, polarizing, divided political scenario.

12:51.911 --> 12:52.611
And what did he do?

12:52.651 --> 12:53.873
He didn't choose sides.

12:55.014 --> 12:57.938
He came announcing the kingdom of God.

12:59.010 --> 13:01.113
He said, repair all of you, every one of you.

13:03.877 --> 13:09.304
And enter into this new way of life, a new kingdom, a better kingdom is here.

13:09.325 --> 13:15.693
And let me tell you today, everything about worldly kingdoms are coming unglued.

13:16.915 --> 13:17.917
And it will, it ought to.

13:18.117 --> 13:24.626
The Bible says in Hebrews, everything that can be shaken will be shaken so that

13:24.866 --> 13:30.174
The only thing that remains is a kingdom that cannot be shaken, and that is a kingdom of our eternal God.

13:32.256 --> 13:44.694
And it is good for us to remember that we are citizens of that kingdom, and of that kingdom, and it's the only kingdom that will last for all eternity long.

13:44.714 --> 13:50.322
There are two scenes we're gonna look at today to see how Jesus engaged in the politics of his day

13:51.426 --> 13:58.537
And fascinating enough, these two conversations, these two scenes happen in the same week of Jesus' life.

13:59.979 --> 14:03.063
It happens in the last week of his life that would lead to the cross.

14:04.005 --> 14:09.072
It's past over a week and the Pharisees and the religious leaders are wanting to get Jesus arrested.

14:09.112 --> 14:13.358
So look at this conversation number one that takes place in Mark chapter 12.

14:15.622 --> 14:21.170
Mark 12 verse 13 says, then they sent some of the Pharisees and the Herodians

14:21.666 --> 14:23.868
to Jesus to trap him and his words.

14:23.889 --> 14:28.934
Now, you couldn't get more different than the Pharisees and the Herodians on the political spectrum.

14:29.235 --> 14:33.700
The Pharisees were far right-winged and the Herodians were far left-winged.

14:34.360 --> 14:38.265
They would never be found in the same room except now they have a common enemy.

14:38.285 --> 14:38.885
It's amazing.

14:38.925 --> 14:40.707
Jesus brings people together no matter what.

14:42.029 --> 14:46.354
Now both of these groups have come together to trap Jesus in his words.

14:47.575 --> 14:50.098
When they came, they said to him, teacher,

14:50.306 --> 14:58.400
We know you are truthful and don't care what anyone thinks, nor do you show partiality but teased away of God truthfully.

14:58.420 --> 15:01.044
Now that's just flattery and pleasantry.

15:03.108 --> 15:03.809
Is it lawful?

15:03.829 --> 15:05.211
Now they've got a question for Jesus.

15:05.432 --> 15:08.797
Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar or not?

15:10.039 --> 15:12.564
Should we pay or shouldn't we?

15:14.367 --> 15:16.370
They've got a question around taxation.

15:16.642 --> 15:26.314
and Rome had all kinds of strange, severe taxes on the Jewish people, many times just to remind them, who was in charge, that Rome owned everything they belonged.

15:27.816 --> 15:33.223
And now, the Pharisees believe they've got a plan to warrant the arrest of Jesus.

15:33.743 --> 15:35.626
They've cooked up a perfect plan.

15:36.427 --> 15:45.618
They come to Jesus, who's a Jewish rabbi, speak into a Jewish audience, and they've got this question, should we pay tax to this gentile

15:45.730 --> 15:50.856
pagan emperor who claims to be divine or shouldn't we?

15:52.118 --> 15:55.342
They know that certainly Jesus will say, no, no, no, don't pay him tax.

15:56.303 --> 16:06.515
And when he does the Herodians who have direct access to King Herod will go to him until King Herod, hey, we found a rebel who is going against Rome.

16:06.756 --> 16:10.881
He is causing people to not pay taxes and break the law of Rome.

16:11.601 --> 16:15.346
And Herod will go to Pilate who is in town for Passover week.

16:16.002 --> 16:18.185
and they will arrest and take Jesus away.

16:18.305 --> 16:19.246
It's a win situation.

16:20.908 --> 16:31.640
And if for some reason, Jesus says, yes, you should pay tax, that Jesus would have immediately lost all his influence with this Jewish audience.

16:32.762 --> 16:34.444
And his movement would come to an end.

16:34.544 --> 16:35.725
It's a win-win situation.

16:36.026 --> 16:39.189
So what does Jesus say in response?

16:39.850 --> 16:40.691
I love verse 15.

16:41.332 --> 16:43.154
He sees right through their pleasant tree.

16:43.266 --> 16:47.051
and false flattery, but knowing their hypocrisy.

16:47.291 --> 16:51.136
Jesus sees their heart, knowing their hypocrisy.

16:51.176 --> 16:53.619
He said to them, why are you testing me?

16:54.881 --> 16:56.783
Bring me a denarius to look at.

16:57.784 --> 17:04.052
And they brought a coin, and Jesus asked them this question, whose image and inscription is this?

17:04.633 --> 17:05.194
He asked them.

17:05.935 --> 17:07.356
Caesars, they replied.

17:08.979 --> 17:11.762
Here is a first century denarius.

17:12.130 --> 17:20.958
the image and inscription of Tiberius, Caesar Tiberius, and it literally calls Tiberius, son of God, king and high priest.

17:21.879 --> 17:25.343
Counterfeit titles to what the scriptures give Jesus.

17:26.964 --> 17:33.250
And so Jesus says, give me a coin, and the coin literally has the image of Caesar and inscription of Caesar on it.

17:33.590 --> 17:39.256
So verse 17, Jesus told them, give to Caesar the things that are Caesars.

17:40.377 --> 17:41.618
And to God,

17:41.762 --> 17:46.928
the things that are gods, and they were utterly amazed at him.

17:48.429 --> 17:51.873
Jesus says, Brimia, coin, looks at the coin, whose image is on it, Caesar's.

17:53.114 --> 17:57.839
And Jesus sets a principle and asks a question at the same time.

17:58.640 --> 18:11.314
The principle he sets forth is, if Caesar's image is on the coin, give him the coin, meaning whoever bears the image on the coin, whoever's image is on the coin, the coin belongs to him or her.

18:12.450 --> 18:18.998
That's the principle, whoever bears the image, the coin, the item belongs to that person whose image is on it.

18:19.438 --> 18:27.527
But the question he's asking is this, if Caesar's image is on the coin, then whose image is on you?

18:29.410 --> 18:32.093
Because he says, give to Caesar what belongs to Caesar.

18:32.113 --> 18:33.254
How do you know this belongs to Caesar?

18:33.274 --> 18:34.035
His image is on it.

18:34.295 --> 18:36.338
But give to God's, what is God's?

18:36.358 --> 18:38.060
Well, how do you know what belongs to God?

18:38.720 --> 18:40.242
What has God's image on it?

18:42.530 --> 18:48.098
And the Pharisees and the Herodians both know we bear the image of God.

18:49.520 --> 18:50.983
God's image is on us.

18:51.063 --> 18:53.166
His imprint is on us.

18:54.327 --> 18:56.811
And so Jesus is saying, you want to talk about tax?

18:56.831 --> 18:57.712
You want to talk about coin?

18:57.993 --> 18:59.856
If Caesar's image is on it, give it to him.

19:00.156 --> 19:01.859
But let me ask you a more important question.

19:02.239 --> 19:03.601
Who's image is on you?

19:04.042 --> 19:05.244
God's image is on you.

19:05.264 --> 19:09.730
So give Caesar the coin, but give your whole life to God.

19:10.972 --> 19:12.274
Give your whole life to God.

19:15.298 --> 19:21.207
Jesus is doing something significant in the world of government and politics here in this passage.

19:22.590 --> 19:28.479
Because until now, government claimed absolute allegiance and total authority over people.

19:29.400 --> 19:30.943
Emperors called themselves God.

19:31.223 --> 19:35.029
They believed they were divine in nature and whatever they said goes.

19:35.751 --> 19:42.962
But Jesus in this moment is drawing a boundary around the allegiance we give the government and the authority they have.

19:43.202 --> 19:50.450
He is limiting, he is shifting from total allegiance to government to limited allegiance.

19:50.470 --> 19:50.670
Why?

19:52.492 --> 19:57.878
Because the client has a government's image, but the people have God's image.

19:58.679 --> 20:02.323
And he's saying honor the emperor, but worship God.

20:02.723 --> 20:09.010
Submit to government, but your highest allegiance belongs only to God.

20:12.066 --> 20:16.751
He's segmenting and limiting the allegiance we would ever give to our government.

20:18.853 --> 20:23.498
Honor the Emperor, but worship God because his image is on you.

20:23.898 --> 20:34.889
That means there are going to be moments where we live in a day where Caesar and God coexist not because they're equals, but because they share some leadership influence on the world.

20:36.351 --> 20:39.634
And sometimes the way of Caesar goes against the way of God.

20:40.994 --> 20:42.295
But Jesus is teaching us here.

20:42.736 --> 20:47.642
If you give to Caesar what belongs to God, that's called idolatry.

20:50.565 --> 20:54.670
And if you don't give to Caesar what is rightfully his, that's disobedience.

20:56.512 --> 20:59.035
Idolatry is giving to Caesar what only belongs to God.

20:59.735 --> 21:05.442
Our worship, our highest allegiance, our affection, our desire, our passion.

21:07.324 --> 21:08.946
We offer him our life.

21:09.762 --> 21:11.144
because his image is on us.

21:13.448 --> 21:17.433
But what is rightfully belonging to Caesar, we give because that's the way of Jesus.

21:19.597 --> 21:21.620
And that the government goes against the way of God.

21:21.700 --> 21:24.805
If the way of Caesar goes against the way of God, we don't follow Caesar.

21:24.825 --> 21:26.307
We follow God all the way through.

21:26.948 --> 21:32.877
No matter what, we follow him because his image is on you and it's on me.

21:36.121 --> 21:39.186
A few days from this conversation, Jesus is arrested.

21:40.834 --> 21:44.959
He is tried and marked trial in front of the government of his day.

21:46.562 --> 21:57.917
And now we're about to go to Mark 15, where we see in the same room, all of the religious and political leaders of the day, and Jesus is standing right there in between them.

21:59.419 --> 22:05.106
Notice what Mark 15, verse one reads, as soon as it was morning,

22:05.986 --> 22:11.853
Having held a meeting, notice all the groups of people with the elders scribes, the whole Sanhedrin.

22:12.414 --> 22:18.461
The chief priests tied Jesus up, led him away, and handed him over to Pilate.

22:19.182 --> 22:24.509
You've got the convergence of all of modern-day leaders in Jesus' time.

22:25.410 --> 22:28.994
Religious leaders, Pilate is there, and Jesus stands among them.

22:29.995 --> 22:35.442
Verse two, so Pilate asked him, are you the king of the Jews?

22:36.674 --> 22:38.876
This is not a religious question for Pilate.

22:39.116 --> 22:41.399
This is not a theological question for Pilate.

22:41.699 --> 22:44.742
This is strictly a political question from Pilate.

22:44.762 --> 22:46.724
Jesus, are you a political leader?

22:47.405 --> 22:48.786
Are you the king of the Jews?

22:49.066 --> 22:53.170
Have you come to take power from me, political power from me?

22:55.453 --> 22:57.034
And notice how Jesus responds.

22:57.895 --> 22:59.216
You say so.

23:00.738 --> 23:03.100
It's the most ambiguous response you can ever think.

23:03.961 --> 23:05.042
You say so.

23:07.138 --> 23:13.025
Tim Keller, the late Tim Keller said about this passage, if Pilate were to ask this question of Buddha, are you a king?

23:13.105 --> 23:13.986
Are you a political leader?

23:14.286 --> 23:15.107
His answer would be no.

23:16.769 --> 23:19.853
If Pilate were to ask this question of Muhammad, are you a political leader?

23:20.113 --> 23:21.095
His answer would be yes.

23:23.197 --> 23:26.401
But when this question is asked of Jesus, he says, you say so.

23:28.964 --> 23:31.747
Meaning time will tell what kind of king I really am.

23:33.089 --> 23:34.130
Jesus could have said,

23:34.402 --> 23:35.724
I'm not the king of the Jews.

23:35.824 --> 23:36.885
I'm not a political leader.

23:36.945 --> 23:45.838
I'm just a spiritual leader, but that wouldn't be true because the movement of Jesus and the message of Jesus impacted politics.

23:45.878 --> 23:52.046
And within a few centuries, the social and political order of the day were turned upside down because of Jesus and his message.

23:53.528 --> 23:57.874
If Jesus were to say, I am a political leader, that wouldn't be true either.

23:58.114 --> 24:01.018
Because Jesus is not the kind of king that Pilate thinks he is.

24:01.578 --> 24:05.123
Pilate has no category for the kingship Jesus is carrying.

24:06.424 --> 24:09.668
So that's why Jesus neither affirms nor denies or does both.

24:11.510 --> 24:17.137
And he says, you say so with the emphasis on you, you will see the kind of king I am.

24:18.879 --> 24:22.564
Verse three, and the chief priests accused him of many things.

24:24.046 --> 24:25.568
Pilate questioned him again.

24:25.988 --> 24:27.570
Are you going to answer?

24:28.482 --> 24:30.925
Look how many things they are accusing you of.

24:31.666 --> 24:33.709
But Jesus did not answer.

24:33.769 --> 24:36.953
And so Pilate was amazed.

24:37.954 --> 24:40.578
Pilate wants Jesus to fight back.

24:41.259 --> 24:44.483
He wants Jesus to defend himself.

24:45.264 --> 24:46.946
The enemies of Jesus are stirred.

24:47.266 --> 24:48.828
Pilate is demanding an answer.

24:49.069 --> 24:50.030
And what does Jesus do?

24:50.070 --> 24:51.011
Nothing.

24:52.954 --> 24:54.075
He doesn't respond.

24:54.556 --> 24:56.338
He is silent.

24:57.730 --> 25:00.713
And the text says that Jesus is silence.

25:02.174 --> 25:03.736
Amazed pilot.

25:05.838 --> 25:10.982
The literal connotation there is pilot stood in wonder and marveled at Jesus.

25:11.323 --> 25:14.966
Because here Jesus is surrounded by the powers of his day.

25:15.266 --> 25:16.608
And the room was pilot.

25:16.848 --> 25:18.930
They're berating him, accusing him.

25:18.990 --> 25:20.651
Jesus can't say something back.

25:20.912 --> 25:22.773
Pilot thinks he should say something back.

25:23.054 --> 25:27.698
But Jesus is found in this moment with such deep inner peace.

25:29.090 --> 25:33.555
He knows who he is, where he's come from, where he's going.

25:35.538 --> 25:39.543
And Jesus does not respond to their accusations.

25:40.924 --> 25:44.329
Jesus cannot be baited into a response.

25:46.691 --> 25:48.954
He stands still and says nothing.

25:51.157 --> 25:53.319
And Pilate was amazed.

25:54.661 --> 25:56.623
There's a really practical application for the church.

25:57.444 --> 25:58.706
It's gonna blow your mind.

25:59.074 --> 25:59.795
It's gonna change your world.

26:00.416 --> 26:00.816
And here it is.

26:02.198 --> 26:04.401
There are sometimes where you don't have to say anything back.

26:06.864 --> 26:11.410
You can follow the example of Jesus and just not say anything sometimes.

26:12.871 --> 26:14.674
You don't have to comment on every post.

26:14.954 --> 26:16.376
I know you thought you did, but you don't have to.

26:16.416 --> 26:22.944
You don't have to respond to every DM or answer every single question asked of you.

26:22.984 --> 26:27.570
You can follow the example of your savior, Jesus,

26:27.650 --> 26:33.999
Stand in the middle as the world is going crazy and just not say anything.

26:35.721 --> 26:42.550
What if silence sometimes, not always, what if silence sometimes is the best answer you could give?

26:45.234 --> 26:46.576
And it's not because we don't care.

26:46.596 --> 26:51.282
No, no, it's because we have found an inner peace.

26:52.130 --> 26:55.473
It's because we have read the end of the story.

26:55.694 --> 26:57.115
We know how it's going to end.

26:57.175 --> 27:02.120
And if you are in Christ, it's going to end really beautifully and really wonderfully.

27:03.121 --> 27:05.443
We know that Jesus cannot be dethroned.

27:05.704 --> 27:06.765
He is on the throne.

27:06.945 --> 27:08.927
He is King of Kings, Lord of Lords.

27:09.007 --> 27:10.248
Every eye will see Him.

27:10.508 --> 27:14.112
And one day, righteousness and justice will be fully restored.

27:14.132 --> 27:17.195
And the Church of Jesus will reign forever with Him.

27:17.516 --> 27:20.018
This is a story of hope that God is writing.

27:21.442 --> 27:34.866
Therefore, as the world comes unglued, we can remain steady in our core, found to be at this unshakable peace, and not have to respond to everything.

27:36.288 --> 27:37.731
I want you to hear me, followers of Jesus.

27:38.212 --> 27:46.226
Followers of Jesus today should be the most non-anxious people in a politically anxious world.

27:47.618 --> 28:00.658
If you are in Christ, if you belong to this kingdom that is a better kingdom, a lasting kingdom, you and I, we are to be the most non-anxious people in a politically anxious world, in a financially anxious world.

28:01.819 --> 28:02.120
Why?

28:02.520 --> 28:04.423
Because we know the end of the story.

28:05.825 --> 28:09.811
And we win, we can trust in him, we can trust in his way.

28:09.851 --> 28:12.275
It ends well.

28:13.417 --> 28:17.042
It's a what if your peace

28:17.218 --> 28:22.183
in a chaotic time became the greatest apologetic to your faith.

28:24.405 --> 28:32.753
What if people around you who don't quite get Jesus yet, but they know you, they're amazed like Pilate was.

28:34.315 --> 28:38.679
They're led to stand and wonder, man, why isn't she freaking out?

28:40.581 --> 28:42.262
Why isn't he coming undone?

28:42.282 --> 28:46.226
It's because you've discovered inner peace.

28:47.234 --> 28:51.480
and let your peace cause wonder in the world.

28:53.103 --> 28:59.372
The story goes on in verse six, and we're introduced to another Jewish leader, a zealot named Barabbas.

29:01.015 --> 29:05.181
At the festival, Pilate used to release for the people a prisoner whom they requested.

29:05.241 --> 29:13.554
There was one named Barabbas who was in prison with rebels who committed murder during their rebellion.

29:14.274 --> 29:18.499
The crowd came up and began to ask Pilate to do for them as was his custom.

29:19.219 --> 29:23.324
And Pilate answered them, do you want me to release the king of the Jews for you?

29:24.245 --> 29:28.310
For he knew it was because of the envy that the chief priests had handed him over.

29:29.471 --> 29:34.076
But the chief priests stirred up the crowd so that he would release Barabbas to them instead.

29:35.538 --> 29:39.982
Pilate asked them again, then what do you want me to do with the one you call the king of the Jews?

29:40.984 --> 29:43.186
Again, they shouted, crucify him.

29:44.930 --> 29:46.072
Pilate said to them, why?

29:46.112 --> 29:47.774
What has he done wrong?

29:48.075 --> 29:51.139
But they shouted all the more crucified him.

29:51.199 --> 29:56.707
In wanting to satisfy the crowd, Pilate released Barabbas to them.

29:56.727 --> 30:02.836
And after having Jesus flogged, he handed him over to be crucified.

30:05.420 --> 30:07.703
We're introduced to a zealot named Barabbas.

30:08.144 --> 30:12.210
In fact, we're told here he was well known as a rebel, as a murderer.

30:12.642 --> 30:17.527
He is in the custody of Pilate because of violence, vengeance.

30:20.891 --> 30:28.860
And here, Pilate wants to release Barabbas, but the crowd is demanding the release of Jesus.

30:30.622 --> 30:41.234
And in this scene, Matthew, when he writes his account, he includes a very interesting detail that I want you to notice about Barabbas.

30:41.826 --> 30:44.148
Look at Matthew 27 verse 16.

30:45.089 --> 30:47.451
At that time, they had a well-known prisoner.

30:47.511 --> 30:52.977
So Barabbas is infamous for all the stuff he's done, a well-known prisoner whose name was what?

30:54.318 --> 30:54.718
Say it again.

30:55.399 --> 30:56.580
All campuses, what was his name?

30:57.982 --> 31:01.765
Jesus, Barabbas.

31:01.785 --> 31:05.088
It wasn't just Barabbas, his name was Jesus, Barabbas.

31:05.209 --> 31:07.150
Jesus was a common name in first century.

31:07.451 --> 31:10.834
And now here in Pilate's custody,

31:11.074 --> 31:14.738
He doesn't just have one Jesus, he's got two Jesuses.

31:15.499 --> 31:16.280
Talk about trouble.

31:18.002 --> 31:20.304
He's got Jesus Barabbas, so verse 17.

31:20.524 --> 31:25.670
So when the crowd had gathered, Pilate asked them, which one do you want me to release to you?

31:26.130 --> 31:31.376
Jesus Barabbas, or Jesus, who is called the Messiah.

31:33.058 --> 31:36.582
Pilate's got two Jesuses on his hands.

31:37.903 --> 31:40.626
Jesus, a murderer, the one called Barabbas.

31:40.866 --> 31:42.168
and Jesus the Messiah.

31:43.230 --> 31:48.618
Get this, Barabbas literally means son of the Father, bar son, Abba Father.

31:50.120 --> 31:52.744
Barabbas' name means son of the Father.

31:52.764 --> 32:01.397
So you got a murderer whose name means son of the Father, and then you got the Messiah who is literally the only begotten son of the Father.

32:03.581 --> 32:09.650
Pilate doesn't just have one Jesus on his hands, he's got two Jesus' on his hands.

32:11.234 --> 32:13.077
But what's fascinating, fam, is this.

32:15.822 --> 32:21.512
Both Jesus Barabbas and Jesus the Messiah, they both want to change the world.

32:24.537 --> 32:26.260
They're both not okay with status quo.

32:26.741 --> 32:33.312
They're both revolutionary leaders in their day and time, immersed in the social and political climate of their day.

32:33.553 --> 32:36.498
They both want to see change in the world

32:37.026 --> 32:37.948
But here's the deal.

32:38.348 --> 32:48.267
Jesus, Barabbas, and Jesus the Messiah, they represent for us two diametrically opposed paths to bringing change in the world.

32:49.909 --> 33:01.170
Jesus, Barabbas, and Jesus Messiah, they represent, they show us, they invite us into two diametrically opposed paths to the change we want to see in the world.

33:02.050 --> 33:07.696
Jesus Barabbas, on one hand, he is fueled by hatred, violence, hostility, and revenge.

33:08.537 --> 33:14.563
He wants to burn the empire down, destroy everyone he can see, who is in his way.

33:16.806 --> 33:21.331
Jesus Barabbas sees people as enemies to be destroyed and eliminated.

33:23.713 --> 33:25.635
On the other hand, you have Jesus the Messiah.

33:28.979 --> 33:30.220
He doesn't want to destroy his enemies.

33:30.260 --> 33:31.762
He wants to save his enemies.

33:32.578 --> 33:34.480
He came to die for his enemies.

33:35.561 --> 33:37.904
Jesus is not motivated by revenge or vengeance.

33:38.625 --> 33:40.788
He's motivated by love and righteousness.

33:42.530 --> 33:44.712
Jesus isn't killing people.

33:44.772 --> 33:46.094
He's raising the dead.

33:46.134 --> 33:50.379
He's not taking from the poor and marginalised.

33:50.619 --> 33:56.786
He's feeding the poor, healing the sick, inviting people to himself.

33:58.114 --> 34:01.137
Oh, Pilate has two, Jesus is on his hands.

34:01.597 --> 34:05.021
Jesus the Messiah and Jesus the murderer.

34:07.543 --> 34:08.804
But who do the crowds choose?

34:11.106 --> 34:12.007
Who do the crowds want?

34:12.428 --> 34:18.534
They need Jesus the Messiah, but they want Jesus Barabbas.

34:20.555 --> 34:24.039
Jesus is who they need, but Barabbas is who they want.

34:25.620 --> 34:27.442
And so they cried out,

34:27.522 --> 34:30.146
Crucify Jesus and give us Barabbas.

34:31.568 --> 34:39.158
They know what to do with a rebel like Barabbas who takes life, but they've got no clue what to do with Jesus who raises the dead.

34:41.582 --> 34:52.057
So Pilate releases Barabbas and takes in custody of Jesus because the crowd chose to have a murderer rather than a merciful one.

34:53.018 --> 34:55.922
They chose the guilty over the innocent

34:56.322 --> 34:59.207
They chose for themselves a rebel instead of a redeemer.

35:02.373 --> 35:06.019
And Jesus steps in as a substitute for Barabbas.

35:06.941 --> 35:08.464
It took literally his place.

35:09.565 --> 35:11.629
And isn't that a beautiful picture of the gospel?

35:12.611 --> 35:16.658
I know you don't want to admit it, but you and I are the Barabbas in the story.

35:17.474 --> 35:26.727
We're the ones who've broken God's law, who deserve punishment because of our sin and our rebellion against God, but Jesus came to stand in our place.

35:27.287 --> 35:28.589
You were released.

35:28.649 --> 35:33.175
He paid the debt you owed, the punishment we incurred on the cross.

35:33.215 --> 35:38.002
He took our payment, fully paid, and He says to you, you're free to go.

35:38.242 --> 35:42.488
You were forgiven, you were righteous, and I will pay the punishment.

35:42.528 --> 35:46.213
You owe Jesus substituted in our place for us.

35:46.393 --> 35:46.733
Amen?

35:47.114 --> 35:48.576
That's the beauty of the gospel.

35:49.858 --> 35:52.822
We will let go free, and Jesus took our place.

35:54.904 --> 35:55.425
But here's the deal.

35:55.866 --> 36:08.082
Just as Pilate had two, Jesus' in custody, you and I, every single day in the way we engage in politics, we have these two paths in front of us.

36:09.794 --> 36:12.477
We have the way of Barabbas or the way of Jesus.

36:13.277 --> 36:18.222
In the way we engage with people who disagree from us, with us.

36:18.242 --> 36:20.544
Even if they wanna crucify you, call your names, whatever.

36:21.005 --> 36:24.648
In the way we engage with people, two options remain.

36:24.708 --> 36:27.891
The way of Barabbas or the way of Jesus.

36:28.452 --> 36:34.898
The way of Barabbas is the way of the world, fueled by hatred, hostility and revenge.

36:35.638 --> 36:39.442
The way of Barabbas is, if someone stands in your way,

36:40.162 --> 36:40.743
Run them over.

36:42.304 --> 36:44.787
No matter what you got to do, there is no justice.

36:45.028 --> 36:47.490
There is no compass of what is right, morally or wrong.

36:48.572 --> 36:51.615
Do whatever it takes to win, because it's all about winning.

36:52.456 --> 36:58.683
So lie if you've got to cheat, if you've got to destroy those who get in your way, because anyone who opposes you is an enemy.

36:58.984 --> 37:00.225
That's the way of Barabbas.

37:00.886 --> 37:08.114
It is tribal, greedy, vengeful, seeking to destroy anyone who gets in their way.

37:09.122 --> 37:12.267
The way of Barabbas is the way of the world, but hear me.

37:12.608 --> 37:15.111
The way of Jesus is the way of the cross.

37:16.674 --> 37:19.158
The way of Jesus is the way of the cross.

37:20.019 --> 37:24.066
It is an upside down kingdom where you pray for your enemies.

37:25.147 --> 37:27.191
You bless those who persecute you.

37:27.211 --> 37:29.795
You turn the other cheek, you go the extra mile.

37:30.696 --> 37:34.482
The way of the cross is to destroy enemies, but to love your enemies.

37:34.946 --> 37:38.950
It is a path of forgiveness, service, and sacrifice.

37:39.331 --> 37:44.857
The way of the cross does not achieve rightful positions or rightful power by earthly means.

37:46.719 --> 37:50.944
That was Jesus' temptation in the wilderness to achieve His rightful power through earthly means.

37:51.024 --> 37:51.264
No, no, no.

37:51.524 --> 37:55.328
The way of the cross trusts in God to be the vindicator, not ourselves.

37:58.131 --> 38:01.215
The way of the cross doesn't keep score.

38:01.495 --> 38:02.616
It is not self-seeking.

38:02.917 --> 38:04.178
It is self-giving.

38:05.666 --> 38:10.991
Let me tell you this, ultimately, the way of the cross isn't about saving a nation.

38:11.752 --> 38:14.935
It's about saving people from every nation tribe and tongue.

38:16.437 --> 38:24.425
So that across the earth, there are people, followers of Jesus, who believe in the message of the cross.

38:27.047 --> 38:33.714
So this week, I want to encourage you, engage in politics, be active, do all of that, but ask yourself this simple question.

38:34.434 --> 38:39.479
Do I resemble the way of Barabbas or the way of Jesus?

38:40.760 --> 38:44.644
Do my actions and attitudes, do they make sense with the way of the cross?

38:45.065 --> 38:48.908
What kind of a revolutionary leader will I be?

38:48.968 --> 38:52.452
Barabbas are Jesus.

38:54.394 --> 38:55.175
Here's what you gotta know.

38:56.256 --> 38:57.917
The world loves Barabbas's.

39:00.160 --> 39:02.642
In fact, they'll want you to be a Barabbas.

39:03.682 --> 39:06.386
Because in the eyes of the world, it's Barabbas who win.

39:06.446 --> 39:09.211
The crowd is demanding, give us Barabbas.

39:11.334 --> 39:16.242
But in the long term, Barabbas may cause a scene, but they don't change the world.

39:17.784 --> 39:31.986
Because 40 years from this moment, the way if Barabbas failed, and Jerusalem was destroyed by the Romans because of people like Barabbas, and all of the other entities in Jerusalem failed

39:32.994 --> 39:35.358
because they rejected the message of the cross.

39:38.703 --> 39:47.398
Sometimes the way of the cross looks like losing in the eyes of the world, but it is the only path to lasting victory.

39:49.261 --> 39:52.626
The message of the cross, the Bible says, is foolishness to the world.

39:52.930 --> 39:57.915
but to those of us who believe it is the power of God unto salvation.

39:58.235 --> 39:59.556
It is what changes people.

39:59.797 --> 40:01.018
It is what changes nations.

40:01.398 --> 40:02.719
It is what changes the world.

40:04.701 --> 40:19.596
So 2,000 years later from that moment, there are no disciples of Barabbas, but there are billions of people across the last 2,000 years who have placed their faith in Christ because the way of the cross stands, the way of Jesus triumphs over everything else, amen?

40:19.656 --> 40:22.098
So choose this day.

40:22.498 --> 40:31.651
The way of Jesus, the way of the cross, and refuse the temptation from the world, or from ourself, to pursue the way of Barabbas.

40:31.671 --> 40:36.217
But there are some of you today, before you can choose the way of Jesus, you must choose Jesus himself.

40:37.999 --> 40:44.608
I'm asking you today, would you give your heart to Christ, the one who took your place, paid hard debt.

40:45.069 --> 40:51.538
This is the moment to surrender your heart to Christ, and allow him to reframe every area of your life.

40:52.066 --> 40:52.887
Would you buy your heads with me?

40:54.148 --> 41:12.766
Father, we ask for your help today, tomorrow, and this week, and all the way to November and beyond, that we will be a people marked by the way of Jesus, the message of the cross, fulllessness of the world, but the power of God for salvation, and a transformation.

41:14.568 --> 41:20.434
So God, may we be shaped by you in how we engage every area of life, including politics,

41:21.378 --> 41:43.039
Fueled not by anger and hatred, but by love, righteousness and justice, serving you and your kingdom, following God, not Caesar, trusting in your wisdom your plan, found to be in the united posture, loving one another, serving our world, reaching the lost, trusting you in the midst of it all.

41:44.460 --> 41:50.706
And may we be a people who would cause wonder in the world because we are at peace.

41:52.386 --> 41:54.130
simply because of who you are.

41:55.212 --> 42:04.534
And today, if there's someone, God, who has yet to experience this peace, would you invite us into that, into this kingdom of Jesus, following Jesus as Lord of all?

42:05.396 --> 42:09.906
All this in the name of Jesus, we pray it in the church, set together, aloud, amen, amen.

